Daimler Plans to Hire 10,000 People on Car Demand, Bild Says

-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 
2011-02-23T19:51:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-23/daimler-plans-to-hire-10-000-people-on-car-demand-bild-says.html
  Daimler AG  plans to recruit 10,000
new employees globally this year because of strong demand for
its cars,  Bild-Zeitung  reported, citing an interview with Chief
Executive Officer Dieter Zetsche.  The company will add 4,000 of the new jobs in  Germany ,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kenneth Wong in Berlin at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net  